\lim_{(x,y)\to(0,0)}  {xy \over \sqrt{x^2 + y^2}} = 0.
0
(x,y)\rightarrow 0
|x| = \sqrt{x^2} \le \sqrt{x^2 + y^2}
\left\vert\frac{xy}{\sqrt{x^2 + y^2}}\right\vert = \frac{|x|}{\sqrt{x^2 + y^2}}|y|\le |y|
x = r \cos(\theta)
y = r \sin(\theta)
\sqrt{x^2 + y^2} = r
f(x,y) = \dfrac{xy}{\sqrt{x^2 + y^2}}
F(r,\theta) = f(r \cos(\theta), r \sin(\theta)) = \dfrac{r^2 \cos(\theta) \sin(\theta)}{r} = r \cos(\theta) \sin(\theta)
(x,y) \to (0,0) \implies r \to 0
